					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The DPCM glitch affects reads, not writes.  Since it's reading $2007, it's likely getting an extra read and blowing past whatever address it was expecting to read from.<br /><a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php?title=APU_DMC&amp;redirect=no#Conflict_with_controller_and_PPU_read" class="postlink">https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php?title=APU_DMC&amp;redirect=no#Conflict_with_controller_and_PPU_read</a></div>

