						<div class="postbody">Yes, though it's not very well-timed; the test loop for the sprite 0 hit isn't as tight as it could be (uses LDA, AND, BEQ), and the wait loop doesn't land it in the idle region on the target scanline, so there can be a lot of jitter even without DPCM: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://youtu.be/T4JtnUvhaHo?t=1612">https://youtu.be/T4JtnUvhaHo?t=1612</a><!-- m --><br /><br />If DPCM throws off the timing a bit, do you know how that might result in the behavior in the first video? When the scroll first glitches, the game should be writing $2240 or so to PPU_ADDRESS, but it appears to get set to $2000.</div>

